review_blob: (Cask at Southampton Arms, Gospel Oak, 20 April 2016) Golden colour with brief, white head. Malty, hoppy nose with citrus, grapefruit and biscuits. Malty, hoppy taste with notes of citrus, grapefruit, grass, biscuits and a generous citric bitterness in the finish. Medium body, quite dry. Fresh and tasty. Nice one.
beer_name: Howling Hops Pale XX Superior No.1

review_blob: (Cask at Southampton Arms, Gospel Oak, 20 April 2016) Amber colour with brief, off-white head. Malty, slightly fruity nose with notes of dried fruit, caramel and slightly earthy hops. Malty taste with bread, dried fruit, raisins, hints of yeast and a balanced earthy bitterness in the finish. Medium body, quite dry. Balanced and tasty bitter. Quite nice.

(Cask at Southampton Arms, Gospel Oak, 20 April 2016) Golden colour with foamy, white head. Malty, hoppy nose with citrus, grass and floral hops. Malty taste with notes of biscuits, citrus, grass and a fairly dry finish with a gentle floral bitterness. Light body, quite dry. Fresh and tasty, but on the thin side. Quite nice.

(Cask at Craft Beer Clerkenwell, London, 19 Apr 2016) Black colour with foamy, beige head. Malty, hoppy nose with notes of coffee, chocolate, caramel and grapefruit. Malty, roasted, hoppy taste with coffee, dark chocolate, grapefruit, resin and a generous bitterness in the finish. Medium body, quite dry. Well made black IPA with an almost uncompromising hop presence. Very nice.
beer_name: Northern Monk Dark Arches Black IPA

review_blob: (Cask at Craft Beer Clerkenwell, London, 19 Apr 2016) Reddish brown colour with foamy, off-white head. Malty, hoppy nose with dark bread, orange pee land caramel. Malty, hoppy taste with notes of caramel, raisins, prunes, orange peel and a generous citric bitterness in the finish. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Tasty and well made brown ale with a generous hop character. Nice one.

(Cask at Craft Beer Clerkenwell, London, 19 Apr 2016) Amber colour with foamy, off-white head. Malty, smoky nose with notes of citrus, smoke, bacon and orange peel. Malty, hoppy taste with citrus, grapefruit, orange peel, hints of smoke and a generous citric bitterness. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Quite smoky nose, but the pale ale character takes over in the mouth, making it very well balanced. Tasty and well made. Very nice.

(Cask at Craft Beer Clerkenwell, London, 19 Apr 2016) Amber colour with foamy, off-white head. Malty, slightly fruity nose with caramel, toffee, bread and a touch of sugar. Malty, slightly fruity taste with notes of toffee, caramel, toast, orange peel, a touch of burnt sugar and a gentle bitterness in the finish. Medium body, with a certain sweetness. Fairly "aleish" lager, tasty and quite nice.

(Cask at Craft Beer Covent Garden, London, 19 Apr 2016) Amber colour with foamy, off-white head. Fruity, malty nose with orange, apricots and a touch of rye bread. Malty, fruity taste with notes of apricots, orange, chewy malt and a balanced citric bitterness. Medium body, with a certain sweetness. Balanced and tasty. Quite nice.

(Cask at Craft Beer Covent Garden, London, 19 Apr 2016) Golden amber colour with frothy, white head. Fruity, malty nose with notes of peaches, grass and toast. Fruity, malty taste with apricots, grass, toast and a slightly herbal bitterness with a touch of earthy hops. Medium body, with a slight sweetness. Tasty and well balanced bitter. Quite nice.

(Cask at Craft Beer Covent Garden, London, 19 Apr 2016) Amber colour, slightly hazy, with frothy off-white head. Fruity, malty nose with citrus, apricots, orange peel and a touch of toast. Malty, fruity taste with notes of orange peel, apricots, some toast and a fairly dry finish with a fresh, balanced citric bitterness. Medium body, with just a touch of sweetness. Fresh and tasty. Nice one.

(Bottle) Pitch black colour with dense, dark brown head. Malty, roasted nose with notes of strong black coffee, cacao, liquorice, treacle, tar, asphalt, black rye bread, oak wood and a touch of cognac. Malty, roasted taste with strong black coffee, cacao, dark chocolate, liquorice, sweet soy sauce, oak wood, cognac and a warming finish with some alcohol, a generous coffee bitterness and a touch of cognac. Full body, quite sweet. Thick and oily texture. Hardly subtle, but very tasty and fairly well balanced (considering it carries a certain punch). Excellent beer!

(Bottle) Black colour with brief, bubbly head. Malty, roasted, spicy nose with ginger, liquorice, strong black coffee, soy sauce, cacao, treacle, a hint of smoke, juniper berries and pine needles. Malty, spicy taste with liquorice, soy sauce, ginger, a touch of chilli, espresso, dark chocolate, juniper berries, pine needles, honey and a finish with a smoky chilli touch and a warming alcohol glow. Full body, quite sweet, with a gentle coffee bitterness. Complex, spicy and tasty, but hardly subtle. Very nice.

(Bottle) Golden colour with frothy, white head. Malty nose with notes of grain, bread, boiled vegetables and canned fruit. Malty taste with grain, bread, a touch of sugar and hints of grassy hops in the finish. Thin body, with a touch of sweetness. Thin and unnecessary, but drinkable.

(Bottle) Black colour with dense, beige head. Malty, roasted, woody nose with notes of liquorice, soy sauce, strong black coffee, bourbon, vanilla, tar, salmiac and oak wood. Malty, roasted, vinous taste with strong black coffee, liquorice, soy sauce, tar, bourbon, vanilla, lots of wood and a strong, vinous finish with a generous coffee bitterness. Full body (or rather massive), with a certain sweetness. Massive stout with lots of bourbon and oak and a fair amount of warming alcohol. Not very subtle, but very nice stuff.

(Bottle) Amber colour with frothy, off-white head. Malty, smoky nose with dried fruit, smoked ham, rye bread, a touch of honey and some tobacco. Malty, smoky taste with notes of caramel, dried fruit, smoked ham, tobacco, rye bread, orange peel a gentle floral bitterness in the finish. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Well made rauchbier, with a balanced smoke character. Quite nice.

(Bottle) Dark brown colour, almost black, with frothy beige head. Malty, roasted nose with notes of coffee, caramel, cacao, dark rye bread and a touch of liquorice. Malty, roasted taste with lots of fresh coffee, liquorice, dark chocolate, black rye bread, roasted malt and a generous coffee bitterness in the finish. Full body, with just a touch of sweetness. Fresh an tasty with a generous coffee character (more so in the mouth than in the nose) and alcohol well hidden. Very nice.
beer_name: De Molen Kopi Loewak Coffee Stout (2011-2013)

review_blob: (Bottle) Golden amber colour, slightly hazy, with frothy white head. Malty, fruity nose with notes of apricots, orange, ripe banana, cereal and bread. Malty, fruity taste with orange, apricots, bread, candy sugar, mango, a touch of yeast and hay. Thin body, with a certain sweetness. Overall quite a decent non alcohol weizen, aroma is according to style but it gets a bit thin and sweet on the palate. Quite drinkable.

(Bottle) Dark brown colour with frothy, beige head, leaving traces of lacing. Malty, roasted nose with caramel, chocolate, dark rye bread, a touch of coffee and roasted malt. Malty, roasted taste with coffee, dark chocolate, caramel, a touch of liquorice, black rye bread and a balanced roasty bitterness in a fairly dry finish. Medium body, with just a touch of sweetness. Solid and well made porter. Very nice.

(Bottle) Dark red colour with frothy, pink head. Fruity, sourish nose with dark cherries, almonds and red berries. Fruity, tart taste with notes of sour cherries, almonds, citrus (pink grapefruit, blood orange, orange peel), a touch of oak wood and a dry, tart finish. Medium body, dry. Clean and fresh cherry character and sourness, possibly lacking some of the funky barnyard and cobweb character of the best beers in the style. Nice one.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: (Bottle) Dark brown colour with big, but brief, foamy beige head. Malty, spicy nose with dark fruit, coffee, liquorice, caramel, dark chocolate, orange peel and spices (dried chilli, cinnamon). Malty, spicy taste with notes of caramel, liquorice, black coffee, chocolate, orange peel, spices (chilli, cinnamon, star anise, ginger), burnt sugar and a balanced spicy bitterness in the finish. Almost full body, with a touch of sweetness. Quite powerful and complex, with lots of coffee, chocolate and spices. Nice one.
beer_name: Lost Abbey Mayan Apocalypse Judgment Day

review_blob: (Bottle) Hazy golden colour with lasting, frothy, off-white head. Malty, fruity nose with white bread, lemon, hay, a touch of honey and cereal. Malty, fruity taste with notes of white bread, peaches, honey, hay, citrus, cereal and a mild spicy bitterness. Medium body, with just a touch of sweetness. Mainly grain, hay and some lemon. Apparently lacking some malt character, but decently drinkable.

(Bottle) Hazy brown colour with brief, foamy, beige head. Fruity, vinous nose with notes of caramel, oak wood, raisins, prunes, dates, a touch of brandy and hints of sour cherries. Malty, fruity, vinous taste with caramel, oak wood, hints of brandy, dried fruit, some coffee, chocolate, dark cherries, a gentle spicy bitterness and a light acidity in a vinous finish. Full body, with a certain sweetness. Quite soft and velvety mouthfeel for its strength, with alcohol fairly well hidden. Complex and tasty. Very nice.

(Bottle, from Systembolaget re, 17 March 2016) Black colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with dark chocolate, liquorice, black rye bread, coffee and a touch of raisins. Malty, roasted taste with notes of dark chocolate, liquorice, black rye bread, raisins, coffee, a touch of orange peel, a velvety touch of roasted oats and a balanced roasty bitterness. More than medium body, quite dry. Tasty and well balanced stout. Nice one.

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Black colour with brief, foamy, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with strong sweet coffee, liquorice and caramel. Malty, roasted taste with notes of liquorice, strong black coffee, cacao, molasses, raisins, dark fruit and a generous roasty bitterness in the finish. Full body, thick and fairly oily mouthfeel. A certain sweetness. Solid and well made imperial porter in excellent balance for its strength. Lovely stuff!

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Golden colour with dense, white head. Fruity, hoppy nose with notes of citrus, grapefruit, tropical fruit and grass. Malty, hoppy taste with citrus, grapefruit, lemon, grass, biscuits and a balanced citric, slightly metallic, bitterness in the finish. Light body, quite dry. Possible a bit thin, but fresh and tasty. Quite nice.

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Black colour with hints of ruby. Dense beige head. Malty, sourish nose with caramel, oak wood, raspberries and hints of bourbon. Malty, tart taste with notes mof caramel, balsamic vinegar, red fruit, raspberries, oak wood, vanilla and a sweet and sour finish with fairly low bitterness. More than medium body, with a certain sweetness. Interesting, and more tasty and well balanced than suspected. Nice one.

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Black colour with dense, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with notes of chocolate, coconut and creamy coffee. Malty, roasted taste with chocolate, coffee, coconut, vanilla and a gentle coffee bitterness. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Tasty and well balanced with an interesting coconut/vanilla touch. Nice one.

(Bottle, Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Black colour with dense, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with coffee, liquorice, anise and cacao. Malty, roasted taste with notes of black coffee, bitter cacao, liquorice, soy sauce, star anise and a generous cacao bitterness. Full body, with a certain sweetness. Tasty and well made imperial stout with lots of dark chocolate and liquorice. Alcohol fairly well hidden. Very nice.
beer_name: t IJ Ciel Bleu Imperial Stout

review_blob: (Bottle, Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Hazy yellow colour with dense, white head. Malty, fruity nose with notes of peaches, grass, white bread and fresh hops. Malty, hoppy taste with bread, grass, grapefruit, lemon and a fresh, balanced bitterness in the finish. Medium body, quite dry. Fresh and tasty. Quite nice.

(Bottle) Black colour with big, dense, pale brown head. Roasted, malty nose with notes of chocolate, black coffee, dark cherries, blackberries, liquorice and a touch of tobacco. Malty, roasted taste with black coffee, liquorice, raisins, dark cherries, dark chocolate and a generous cacao bitterness in a finish with a slight cherry tartness. Full body, with a touch of sweetness. Really tasty and interesting with the sour cherry touch to the Hel & Verdoemenis, and quite well balanced. Great stuff!

(Draught at Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 21 Feb 2016) Pale amber colour with frothy, off-white head. Malty, hoppy nose with grain, grapefruit, citrus and apricots. Malty, hoppy taste with notes of grapefruit, tropical fruit, grain, dried apricots and a dry finish with a generous citric bitterness. Medium body, quite dry. Tasty, fresh and well made. Nice one.

(Draught at Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Golden colour with frothy, white head. Malty, fruity nose with canned fruit, peaches, grainy malt and green apples. Malty, fruity taste with notes of canned fruit, citrus, tropical fruit, candy sugar and a gentle spicy bitterness. Almost full body, with a certain sweetness. Fairly well balanced and tasty, but not very complex and hardly exciting. Quite nice.

(Draught at Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Amber colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, fruity nose with notes of orange peel, dried fruit and candy sugar. Malty, fruity taste with orange peel, apricots, caramel and balanced earthy bitterness in the finish. Almost full body, with a certain sweetness. A bit unbalanced, seemingly with more focus on malt and alcohol than on hops. Still, quite nice.

(Draught at Craft & Draft, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Amber colour with dense, off-white head. Malty, fruity nose with orange, grapefruit and crisp-bread. Malty taste with notes of orange, crisp-bread, apricots and a balanced spicy, citric bitterness. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Tasty and well balanced. Quite nice.
beer_name: Detour - Obstinate Disobedience Amber Ale - ORGANIC

review_blob: (Draught at Craft & Draft, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Reddish amber colour with frothy, off-white head. Malty, spicy nose with notes of orange peel, caramel and a touch of oak wood. Malty, spicy taste with orange peel, apricots, oak wood and a balanced spicy bitterness in the finish. Almost full body, with a certain sweetness. Tasty and quite interesting, with a surprising wood touch. Nice one.

(Draught at Craft & Draft, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Black colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, roasted, hoppy nose with black coffee, black rye bread, pine needles and grapefruit. Malty, roasted taste with notes of dark chocolate, black coffee, pine needles, grapefruit and a generous piney bitterness. More than medium body, quite dry. Solid and well made black IPA. Very nice.
beer_name: Tempest In The Dark We Live

review_blob: (Draught at Jopen Proeflokaal, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Golden amber colour with dense, off-white head. Malty, hoppy nose with notes of grapefruit, resin and pine needles. Malty, hoppy taste with grapefruit, resin, grainy malt and a generous citric, resiny bitterness. Almost full body, with balanced sweetness. Possibly a bit sharp and unbalanced, but quite tasty with a generous hop profile. Nice one.

(Draught at Jopen Proeflokaal, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016. Vintage 2013) Black colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with dried fruit, chocolate and toasted wheat. Malty, roasted taste with notes of chocolate, dark bread, caramel, banana and flavours of wheat. Almost full body, with a certain sweetness and a gentle bitterness. Well balanced and warming weizenbock. Nice one.

(Draught at Jopen Proeflokaal, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Amber colour with frothy, off-white head. Malty nose with coffee, citrus, orange, grainy malt ... but mainly coffee. Malty, slightly fruity taste with citrus, orange, coffee, toast and a gentle citric bitterness in a dry finish. Medium body, quite dry. Tasty and well made, with a balanced coffee touch and a fairly low bitterness for an IPA. Quite nice.

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Golden amber colour with dense, off-white head. Malty, spicy nose with bread, hay, grass and earthy hops. Malty, spicy taste with notes of dried fruit, ginger, hints of basil and rosemary, and a sweetish finish with a gentle bitterness and hints of herbs. Medium body, with a certain sweetness. Interesting and quite herbal. Quite nice.

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Black colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with notes of coffee, cacao, black rye bread and tobacco. Malty, roasted taste with coffee, cacao, a touch of smoke and a balanced coffee bitterness in a dryish finish. Medium body, with just a touch of sweetness. Tasty and well balanced porter. Nice one.

(Draught at Beer Temple, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Amber colour with frothy, off-white head. Malty, fruity nose with apricots, orange marmalade and caramel. Malty, hoppy taste with notes of caramel, orange peel, grapefruit and a generous citric, slightly metallic, bitterness in the finish. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Really well made and tasty IPA, and the balanced alcohol level makes it very drinkable. Very nice.

(Draught at In De Wildeman, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Pale amber colour with frothy, white head. Fruity, hoppy nose with notes of apricots, orange, grapefruit and grainy malt. Malty, hoppy taste with grain, orange, grapefruit, pine needles and a generous, fresh, citric bitterness in the finish. Medium body, quite dry. Tasty, well made and highly drinkable ale with a fresh hop profile. Nice one

(Draught at In De Wildeman, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Amber colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, fruity nose with pumpkin, cinnamon, dried fruit and caramel. Malty, fruity taste with notes of caramel, toffee, pumpkin, dried fruit, cinnamon and a balanced spicy bitterness in a slightly sweetish finish. Almost full body, with a certain sweetness. Tasty an well made with a balanced pumpkin character. Quite nice.

(Bottle, De Prael Proeflokaal, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Dark reddish brown colour with frothy, beige head. Malty nose with notes of caramel, dried fruit and dark bread. Malty taste with caramel, toffee, chocolate, dark fruit and a slightly bitter-sweet finish. Medium body, with a certain sweetness and a gentle bitterness. Tasty and well balanced. Quite nice.

(Draught at De Prael Proeflokaal, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Hazy golden colour with frothy, white head. Malty, hoppy nose with white bread, wheat, grass and lemon. Malty, hoppy taste with notes of wheat, grass, citrus, some grapefruit and a fairly sharp citric bitterness in the finish. Medium body, quite dry. Tasty and hoppy with a certain wheat character. Quite nice.
beer_name: De Prael West Indian Pale Ale (WIPA)

review_blob: (Draught at Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Amber colour with dense, off-white head. Fruity, hoppy nose with notes of citrus, grapefruit, orange peel and fresh hops. Malty, fruity taste with caramel, orange marmalade, citrus and fresh floral hops in a finish with a balanced bitterness. Medium body, with a touch of sweetness. Tasty and well made IPA. Nice one.

(Draught at Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 20 Feb 2016) Black colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, roasted nose with caramel, black rye bread, chocolate and roasted grain. Malty, roasted taste with notes of caramel, sweet liquorice, coffee and a gentle spicy bitterness in the finish. Almost full body, quite sweet. Interesting and tasty, quite sweet and leaning in the doppelbock direction. Nice one.

(Bottle) Reddish amber colour with frothy, beige head. Malty, hoppy nose with dried apricots, peaches, orange peel, caramel, honey and pine needles. Malty, fruity taste with notes of caramel, dried apricots, peaches, honey, orange peel and a balanced resiny bitterness in the finish. Medium body, with a certain caramel sweetness. Tasty and well balanced, with a generous hop character. Quiet nice.

(Draught at Arendsnest, Amsterdam, 19 Feb 2016) Hazy amber colour with frothy, off-white head. Malty nose with biscuits, citrus peel, dried fruit and spices. Malty taste with notes of bread, biscuits, orange peel, cinnamon, bread spices, a touch of ginger and balanced spicy bitterness. Almost full body, with a certain sweetness. On the sweet side, but tasty and spicy. Nice one.
